trans-unit.source: O Allah, separate me from my sins as You have separated the East from the West. O Allah, cleanse me of my transgressions as the white garment is cleansed of stains. O Allah, wash away my sins with ice and water and frost.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, da me odvoji od moje grehe, kao da su se razdvojili na istoku sa zapada. O Allah, ocisti me od mog greha, kao beli garment je oиiљжenih mrlje. O Allah, oprati moje grehe sa leda, vode i frost.

trans-unit.source: Glory is to You, O Allah, and praise, Blessed is Your Name and Exalted is Your Majesty, There is none worthy of worship but You.
trans-unit.target: Slava je tebi, O Allah, i pohvale, Blagoslovljena je vaše ime i Exalted je vaše Veličanstvo, niko nije dostojan molitve, ali ti.

trans-unit.source: I turn my face towards the One Who created the heavens and the earth, as a true believer. I am not of those who associate partners with Allah. Verily, my prayer and my devotion, my living and my death, are for Allah, Lord of the worlds, He has no partners. Thus I have been commanded and I am among those who have submitted. O Allah, You are the King, there is none worthy of worship but You. You are my Lord and I am Your slave. I have wronged my own soul and confess my sin. Forgive all of my sins, surely none forgives sins but You. Guide me to the perfection of my character, for none guides to its perfection but You. Protect me from the evils of my character, for none may protect me from its evils but You. I am here at Your service. All goodness is in Your Hands, and evil is not attributed to You. I am (created) by You, and I am (returning) to You. You are Most Blessed, Most Exalted. I seek Your forgiveness and repent to You.
trans-unit.target: Okrenem lice prema jedan koji stvori nebo i zemlju, kao pravi vernik. Ja nisam od onih koji su povezali partneri Alah. Bez ustezanja, moju molitvu i moju odanost, moju dnevnu i moja smrt su za Alaha, Gospode svetova, on ima partnera. Stoga sam bio ljudima, a ja sam među onima koji podnesu. O Allah, ti si kralj, niko nije dostojan molitve, ali ti. Ti si moj gospodar, a ja sam tvoj rob. Ja sam nanosila svoju dušu i prizna moj greh. Oprosti sve moje grehe, sigurno niko ne oprosti grehe ali ti. Vodi me do savršenstvo mog karaktera, jer nijedan vodi do svog perfekcionizma osim tebe. Zaštiti me od zla moj karakter, jer ne može zaštiti od njenih Zala ali ti. Tu sam na usluzi. Sva dobrota je u tvojim rukama, a zlo se ne vezuje za tebe. Ja sam (kreirana) pored tebe, i ja sam (povratak) tebi. Ti si najviše blagoslovljen, najviše izmorenom. Traћim tvoj oprost i Pokajte se tebi.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, Lord of Jibra'il, Mika'il and Israfil. Maker of the heavens and the earth. Knower of the unseen and the seen. You judge between Your slaves regarding that in which they differ. Guide me to the truth regarding that in which there is difference, by Your Leave. Surely, You guide whomever you please to the straight path.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, gospodar Jibra'il, Mika'il i Israfil. Tvorca neba i zemlje. Pravoverac nevidjeno i vidjeno. Ne suditi između svoje robove u vezi u kojoj se oni razlikuju. Vodi me na istinu u vezi toga u kojem ne postoji razlika, od strane vaše ostaviti. Sigurno si Vodič za koga li molim te da pravim putem.

trans-unit.source: Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Allah is the Greatest, Most Great. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Praise is to Allah, abundantly. Glory is to Allah, at the break of day and at its end. (3x). I seek refuge in Allah from Satan, From his breath and from his voice and from his whisper.
trans-unit.target: Allah je najveći, naj. Allah je najveći, naj. Allah je najveći, naj. Pohvala je Alahu, sasvim jasno naglasila. Pohvala je Alahu, sasvim jasno naglasila. Pohvala je Alahu, sasvim jasno naglasila. Slava je Alahu, pred kraj dana, a na njegovom kraju. (3 x). trazim utociste u Alaha od Satane, od njegovog daha njegov glas i sa njegove љapat.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, praise is to You. You are the light of the heavens and the earth and all that they contain. Praise is to You, You are the Sustainer of the heavens and the earth and all they contain. (Praise is to You, You are the Lord of the heavens and the earth and all they contain.) (Praise is to You, Yours is dominion of the heavens and the earth and all they contain.) (Praise is to You, You are the King of the heavens and the earth.) (And praise is to you.) (You are the truth, Your Promise is true, Your Word is true, Your audience is true, Paradise is true, Hell is true, the Prophets are true, and Muhammad (peace and blessings be upon him) is true, and the Hour of Judgement is true.) (O Allah, to You I have submitted, and upon You I depend. I have believed in You and to You I turn in repentence. For Your sake I dispute and by Your standard I judge. Forgive me what I have sent before me and what I have let behind me, what I have concealed and what I have declared.) (You are the One Who sends forth and You are the One Who delays, there is none who has the right to be worshipped but You.) (You are my God, there is none who has the right to be worshipped but You.)
trans-unit.target: O Allah, hvaljen je na tebi. Ti si svjetlo nebesa i zemlje, i sve to sadrže. Pohvala je za tebe, ti si na odrћavanja dinamike nebesa i zemlje, i svi oni sadrže. (Pohvala je za tebe, ti si gospodar nebesa i zemlje, i svi oni sadrže). (Pohvala je za tebe, tvoja je vlast nebesa i zemlje, i svi oni sadrže). (Pohvala tebi, ti si kralj neba i zemlje.) (I pohvala tebi.) (Ti si istina, vaše obećanje je istina, vaša reč je istina, vaša publika je istina, istina je raj, pakao je istina, proroci su ispunjeni i Muhammad (mir i blagoslov nek je s njim) je istina i čas Sudnji je istina). (O Allah, tebi predalo, a oslanjam se na vas. Verovao sam u tebe i da ti ja pretvoriti u repentence. Za tvoje dobro osporavam i prema tvojim standardima sudim. Oprosti šta sam poslao pre mene i šta treba da pusti iza mene, kako da se sakrije i proglasio sam.) (Ti si onaj koji šalje napred-nazad i ti si jedan koji kašnjenja, niko nema pravo da bude obožavao ali ti.) (Ti si moj Bog, ne postoji niko ko ima pravo da bude obožavao ali ti).

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'I know Allah (azza wa jal) better than all of you do'.
trans-unit.target: U saopštenju od proroka (testere): "Znam Allah (azza wa jal) bolje od svih vas".

trans-unit.source: Whoever hates to revert to Kufr.
trans-unit.target: Onaj ko ne voli da se vratite Kufri.

trans-unit.source: The grades in superiority of the believers will be according to their good deeds.
trans-unit.target: Ocene u superiornost vernici će biti prema njihovim dobra dela.

trans-unit.source: Al-Haya is a part of faith.
The statement of Allah (azza wa jal): "But if they repent and perform Iqamat-as-Salat [offer Salat (prayers) perfectly] and give Zakat then leave their way free."
trans-unit.target: U saopštenju od Alaha (azza wa jal): "Ali ako se pokajem i izvršavanje Iqamat kao Vaktija [ponuditi savršeno Vaktija (molitve)] i daj zakata, onda odi do slobode."

trans-unit.source: Whoever says that faith is action (good deeds).
trans-unit.target: Ko god kaže da ta vera je akcija (dobra dela).

trans-unit.source: If one does not embrace Islam truly, but does so by compulsion or for fear of being killed etc.
trans-unit.target: Ako jedan istinski ne prihvati Islam, ali da li tako po prinuda ili iz straha da ne gine itd.

trans-unit.source: To greet is a part of Islam.
To be ungrateful to one's husband. And disbelief is of different grades.
trans-unit.target: Da budem nezahvalan sa svojim muћem. Da, a neverovanje je različite ocena.

trans-unit.source: Sins are from ignorance and a sinner is not a disbeliever unless he worships others along with Allah (azza wa jal).
trans-unit.target: Gresi su iz neznanja i grešnik ne ne veruje ako ne oboћava drugima zajedno sa Allah (azza wa jal).

trans-unit.source: The statement of Allah (azza wa jal): {"If two parties (or groups) from among the believers fall to fighting, then make peace between them both."}4.49
trans-unit.target: U saopštenju od Alaha (azza wa jal): {"Ako ja dve stranke (ili grupe) među vernicima borbe, onda pravi mir izmedju njih oboje."} 449

trans-unit.source: Zulm (wrong) of one kind can be greater or lesser than that of another.
trans-unit.target: Zulm (pogrešno) jedne vrste mogu biti veći ili manji od toga drugoga.

trans-unit.source: To establish prayers on the night of Qadr is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Za uspostavljanje molitve u noжi Qadr je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: Al-Jihad (holy war - fighting in Allah's cause) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Al-Jihad (Sveti rat - borba u Alahovu svrhu) je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: It is a part of faith to establish the (Nawafil - voluntary) prayers during the nights of Ramadan.
trans-unit.target: To je deo vere da uspostavi (Nawafil - dobrovoljna) molitve noću Ramazana.

trans-unit.source: To observe Saum [fasts (according to Islamic teachings)] during the month of Ramadan (sincerely and faithfully) hoping for Allah's rewards only, is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Posmatrati Saum [fasts (prema islamskih učenja)] tokom mesec Ramazan (iskreno i odano) nadaju Alahova nagrađuje samo, je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: (What is said) regarding the deeds of faith.
trans-unit.target: (Šta je rekao je) koji se odnosi na dela vere.

trans-unit.source: The (offering of) Salat (Prayers) is a part of faith.
(What is said regarding the superiority of) a person who embraces Islam sincerely.
trans-unit.target: (Šta je rekao u vezi superiornost) osoba koja iskreno prihvata Islam.

trans-unit.source: Ad-Din (good righteous deed - act of worship) loved most by Allah (azza wa jal) is that which is done regularly.
trans-unit.target: Ad-Din (dobro pravedni delo - akt milosti) ispunim Alaha (azza wa jal) je to koje vrši se redovno.

trans-unit.source: To pay Zakat is a part of Islam.
trans-unit.target: Da platim zakata spada u Islam.

trans-unit.source: To accompany the funeral processions (up to the place of burial) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Da pratim na sahranu povorkama (do mesto sahranu) je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: The fear of a believer that his good deeds may be annulled (lost) without his knowledge.
trans-unit.target: Strah od vernika može da poništi njegova dobra dela (izgubio) bez njegovog znanja.

trans-unit.source: The asking of (angel) Jibrael (Gabriel) from the Prophet (SAWS) about Belief, Islam, Ihsan (perfection).
trans-unit.target: Sa pitanjem od (angel) Jibrael (Gabriel) iz je prorok (testere) o verovanju, Islam, Ihsan (savršenstvo).

trans-unit.source: A Muslim is the one who avoids harming Muslims with his tongue and hands.
trans-unit.target: Musliman je onaj koji se izbegava ošteti Muslimani sa svojim jezikom i rukama.

trans-unit.source: The superiority of that person who leaves all doubtful (unclear) things for the sake of his religion.
trans-unit.target: Superiornost ta osoba koja ostavlja sve upitno (nejasno) stvari u ime svoje religije.

trans-unit.source: To pay Al-Khumus (one-fifth of the war booty to be given in Allah's cause) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Da platim Al-Khumus (jedna petina ratni plen da dobije u Alahovu svrhu) je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: What is said regarding the statement: 'The reward of deeds depends upon the intention.'
trans-unit.target: Šta je rekao u vezi izjavu: 'nagrada za dela zavisi od namera.'

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'Religion is An-Nasiha [(to be sincere and true) to Allah, to His Messenger, to the Muslim rulers, and to all the Muslims.]'
trans-unit.target: Izjavu o proroku (testere): ' religija je na Nasihu [(da budem iskren i istinit) Alahu, njegovo Messenger, muslimanski vladari, i svi Muslimani.] "

trans-unit.source: Whose Islam is the best (Who is the best Muslim)?
trans-unit.target: Čiji Islam je najbolje (ko je najbolji musliman)?

trans-unit.source: To feed (others) is a part of Islam.
To like for one's (Muslim's) brother what one likes for himself is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Kao za jedan (Muslimani) brate tako dopada za sebe je deo vere.

trans-unit.source: To love the Messenger (Muhammad) (SAWS) is a part of faith.
trans-unit.target: Da volim glasnik (Muhammad) (testere) je deo vere.

Retiring to a Mosque for Remembrance of Allah (I'tikaf)
trans-unit.target: U penziju u džamiju za sjećanje Allaha (I'tikaf)

trans-unit.source: Sales in which a Price is paid for Goods to be Delivered Later (As-Salam)
trans-unit.target: Prodaje u kojima je cena je platili za robu da bude dostavljeno kasnije (Es-Selam)

trans-unit.source: Transferance of a Debt from One Person to Another (Al-Hawaala)
trans-unit.target: Transferance duga od jedne osobe na drugu (Al-Hawaala)

trans-unit.source: The Prophet (SAWS) used to take care of the people in preaching by selecting a suitable time so that they might not run away (or get bored).
trans-unit.target: Prorok (testere) koristi se pobrinuti za ljude u propovedanje tako što ćete izabrati pravog vremena, tako da su mogla bi da pobegne (ili postane dosadno).

trans-unit.source: Whoever fixed a special day for giving (a religious talk) to the students.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je popravio poseban dan za davanje (religiozni razgovor) za učenike.

trans-unit.source: If Allah (azza wa jal) wants to do good to a person, He makes him comprehend the religion. [The understanding of the Qur'an and the Sunna (legal ways) of Prophet Muhammad (SAWS)].
trans-unit.target: Ako Alah (azza wa jal) htio dobro osobi, on čini ga shvatiti religiju. [Za razumevanje Kur'anu i Sunna (pravni načini) proroka Muhameda (testere)].

trans-unit.source: Wish to be like the one who has knowledge and Al-Hikmah (wisdom) [i.e. the knowledge of the Qur'an and the Sunna (legal ways) of the Prophet (SAWS)]. And 'Umar (RA) said: Everyone must acquire sound religious knowledge early before he becomes a chief. (Abu 'Abdullah said: The companions of the Prophet had studied inspite of the fact that they were old in age).
trans-unit.target: Voleo bih da bude kao onaj koji ima znanje i Al-Hikmah (mudrost) [odnosno znanje o Kur'anu i Sunna (pravni načini) od proroka (testere)]. I ' ukljuиio (RA) je rekao: svi moraju nabaviti zvučne verskom znanju rano dok ne postane poglavica. (Abu ' Abdulah rekao: kompanjoni proroka studirala uprkos činjenicu da su bili stari u godinama).

trans-unit.source: What has been said about the journey of Prophet Musa ('alaihi as-salam) (when he went) in the sea to meet Al-Khidr.
trans-unit.target: Što je rečeno o putovanje od proroka Musa ('alaihi Es-Selam) (kada je bio) u moru upoznati Al-Khidr.

trans-unit.source: The statement of the Prophet (SAWS): 'O Allah! Bestow on hlm (Ibn 'Abbas) the knowledge of the Book (the Qur'an).'
trans-unit.target: U saopštenju od proroka (testere): "O Allah! Darujete njega (Ibn ' Abbas) znanje o knjizi (Kur'anu). "

trans-unit.source: At what age may youth be listened to (i.e. the quotation of the Hadith from a boy be acceptable).
trans-unit.target: U kojoj godini maja mladost saslušati (odnosno citat od Hadith od momka da bude prihvatljivo).

trans-unit.source: To go out in search of knowledge.
Whoever is asked about knowledge while he is busy in some conversation, so he finished talking and then answered the questioner.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je pitao za znanje, dok je on zauzet u neki razgovor, pa je završila razgovor i onda se javio se ko ispituje.

trans-unit.source: The superiority of a person who learns (Islam, becomes a religions scholar) and then teaches it to others.
trans-unit.target: Superiornost osobe koja uči (Islam, postaje učenjak religije) i zatim je predaje drugim osobama.

trans-unit.source: (What is said regarding) the disappearance of the (religious) knowledge and the appearance of (religious) ignorance.
trans-unit.target: (Šta je rekao koji se odnosi na) o nestanku (religiozni) znanje i izgled (religiozni) neznanje.

trans-unit.source: To give a religious verdict while riding an animal or standing on anything else.
trans-unit.target: Dati presudu religiozni dok jahanje životinja ili stoji nista drugo.

trans-unit.source: Whoever gave a religious verdict by beckoning or by nodding.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je dao presudu religiozne oћivela ili klima glavom.

trans-unit.source: The Prophet (saws) urged the people (mission) of 'Abdul Qais to memorize the faith and the (religious) knowledge (as he explained to them) and to inform (convey) to their people whom they left behind (at home).
trans-unit.target: Prorok (testere) pozvao je građane (misija) ' Abdul Qais da zapamtim veru i (religiozni) znanja (kao što je objasnio da ih) i obavijestiti (, prenesite) njihove osobama u koje su ostavili za sobom (kod kuće).

trans-unit.source: To travel seeking an answer to a problematic matter, and to teach it to one's family.
trans-unit.target: Putovati, tražeći odgovor na problematično pitanje, i naučiti da svoje porodice.

trans-unit.source: To fix the duties in rotation for learning (religious) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: Fi x dužnosti u rotaciju za učenje (religiozni) znanja.

trans-unit.source: To be furious while preaching or teaching if one sees what one hates.
trans-unit.target: Da bude besna dok propovedi ili predaje ako neko vidi kako mrzi.

trans-unit.source: Whoever knelt down before the Imam or a (religious) preacher.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je klekao pre nego što je Imam ili propovednik (religiozni).

trans-unit.source: Whoever raises his voice in (conveying) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: Onaj ko postavlja njegov glas u (prenoseći) znanja.

trans-unit.source: Repeating one's talk thrice in order to make others understand.
trans-unit.target: Ponavlja nečiji razgovor tri puta da bi drugima da shvate.

trans-unit.source: A man teaching (religion to) his woman-slave and his family.
trans-unit.target: Čovek koji predaje (religije da) njegova žena-Rob i njegova porodica.

trans-unit.source: The preaching (and teaching) of the (religious) knowledge to women by the Imam (chief):
trans-unit.target: Je propovedao (i predavanja) (religiozni) znanja da žene od strane imama (glavni):

trans-unit.source: How the (religious) knowledge will he taken away?
Should a day be fixed for women in order to teach them religion (apart from men)?
trans-unit.target: Trebalo bi da dnevno biti popravljena za žene da bi se predavati religija (osim ljudi)?

trans-unit.source: Whoever heard something (but did not understand it) and then asked again till he understood it completely.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je nešto čuo (ali nisam razumeo to) i zatim ponovo pitao dok je to potpuno razumeo.

trans-unit.source: It is incumbent on those who are present [in a religious meeting (or conference)] to convey the knowledge to those who are absent. (This statement has come from the Prophet (SAWS) upon the authority of Ibn 'Abbas).
trans-unit.target: To je sadašnji na one koji su prisutni [u verskim sastanak (ili konferencije)] da prenesem znanje onima koji su odsutni. (Ova izjava je došao iz je prorok (testere) na autoritet Ibn ' Abbas).

trans-unit.source: The sin of a person who tells a lie against the Prophet (SAWS).
trans-unit.target: Greh osobe koja govori da laž protiv proroka (testere).

trans-unit.source: Concerning the variety of words used by narrators conveying different significations regarding the concept of narrating and which has importance for the Hadith scholars only.
trans-unit.target: Što se tiče mnoštvo reči koje narrators koristi prenošenje različitih significations u vezi sa konceptom dana i koji je od značaja za učene u Hadith samo.

trans-unit.source: The knowledge and its teaching and preaching at night.
trans-unit.target: Znanje i njene predaje i propoveda noću.

trans-unit.source: To speak about (religious) knowledge at night.
(What is said regarding) the memorization of the (religious) knowledge.
trans-unit.target: (Šta je rekao koji se odnosi na) poиeti (religiozni) znanja.

trans-unit.source: To be quiet (and listen) to religious learned men.
trans-unit.target: Da cuti (i slušaj) do religije naučio ljude.

trans-unit.source: When a religious learned man is asked. "Who is the most learned person." (It is better for him to attribute or entrust absolute knowledge to Allah (azza wa jal), and to say, "Allah is the Most Learned (than anybody else).")
trans-unit.target: Kada načitanim religiozan je pitao. "Ko je najuиenijih osoba." (To je bolje za njega da pripisuju ili entrust apsolutnog znanja da Allah (azza wa jal) i govoriti: "Allah je najviše naučio (od bilo koga drugog).")

trans-unit.source: Whosoever, while standing, asked a religious learned man who was sitting (on a pulpit or a similar thing, about something).
trans-unit.target: Ko god je, dok smo stajali, pitao načitanim religiozan sedi (na propovedi ili sličnu stvar, o nečemu).

trans-unit.source: To ask about a religious matter and to give a religious verdict (at Mina during Hajj) while doing the Rami of Jimar (throwing of pebbles at the Jimar in Mina during Hajj).
trans-unit.target: Da pitam za religiozno pitanje i dati je religiozni presuda (u Mina tokom Hajj) dok obavljaju Rami Dћimar (bacanje kamenиiжe na Dћimar u Mina tokom Hajj).

trans-unit.source: The Statement of Allah (azza wa jal): "And of knowledge you (mankind) have been given only a little." (V. l7:85).
trans-unit.target: U izjavi od Alaha (azza wa jal): "I znanja (ljudski rod) dobio si samo malo." (V. l7:85).

trans-unit.source: Whosoever left some optional things simply for the fear that some people may not be able to understand them and may fall into something more difficult.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je ostavio neke opcionalne stvari jednostavno zbog straha da neki ljudi možda neće moći da ih razumem i da padne u nešto teže.

trans-unit.source: Whoever selected some people to teach them (religious) knowledge preferring them over others for fear that the others may not understand it.
trans-unit.target: Ko god izabrali neke ljude da im predaje (religiozni) znanja preferirati ih nad drugima, iz straha da drugi mogu shvatiti.

trans-unit.source: The Imam questioning his companions in order to test their knowledge.
trans-unit.target: Imam ispitivanje njegovi saputnici da bi testirali svoje znanje.

trans-unit.source: (What is said as regards:-) To be shy (Al-Haya') while learning (religious knowledge).
trans-unit.target: (Šta je rekao kao Bob Geldof :-) Stidite se (Al-љalimo ') dok učenje (religiozni znanja).

trans-unit.source: Whosoever felt shy (to ask something) and then requested another person to ask on his behalf.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je osetio stidljiv (nešto da pitam) i onda zatražio drugoj osobi da pitam u njegovo ime.

trans-unit.source: Teaching religious knowledge and giving religious verdicts in a mosque.
trans-unit.target: Predaje verskom znanju i daje religiozni presude u džamiji.

trans-unit.source: Whosoever answered to the questioner more than what he asked.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je odgovorila da voli više nego to pitao da pita.

trans-unit.source: What is said regarding the hand to hand exchange (of books of knowledge), and the writing of knowledge by religious scholars to different countries.
trans-unit.target: Šta je rekao u vezi ruke u ruku razmena (knjige znanja) i pisanje znanja religiozni uиenjaci na različite zemlje.

trans-unit.source: Whoever sat at the farther end of a gathering. And whoever found a place amongst a gathering and took his seat there.
trans-unit.target: Ko god je sedeo na kraju dalje okupljanje. I ko god nasli mesto medju okupljanje i uzeo njegovo mesto tamo.

trans-unit.target: U saopštenju od proroka (testere): "Je verovatno da osoba koja prima informaciju indirektno može shvatiti to bolje nego on ko je čuo to direktno iz svojih izvora."

trans-unit.source: I Have Put Trust In Allah

In the name of Allah, the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful! Allah is the greatest, Allah is the greatest, Allah is the greatest, how perfect He is, The One Who has placed this (transport) at our service, and we ourselves would not have been capable of that, and of our Lord is our final destiny. O Allah we ask You for birr and taqwaa(comprehensive terms referring to all good actions and obedience) in this journey of ours, and we ask you for deeds which please You. O Allah, facilitate our journey and let us cover it's distance quickly. O Allah, You are the Companion on the journey and The Successor over the family, O Allah, I take refuge with you from the difficulties of travel, from having a change of hearts and being in a bad predicament, and I take refuge in You from an ill fated out come with wealth and family.
trans-unit.target: U ime Alaha, veoma ljubazan, i najmilostiviji! Alah je najveći, Allah je najveći, Alah je najveći, kako savršen je, The jednog ko je stavio ovu (transport) na naše usluge, mi sami ne bi bio sposoban za to i Gospodnje nam je konačna sudbina. O Allah molimo vas za birr i taqwaa (sveobuhvatnom smislu misleći na sve dobre akcije i pokornosti) na putovanju od naše, i molimo te za dela koja vas molim. O Allah, olakšati naše putovanje i pusti nas da brzo pokriti to je udaljenost. O Allah, ti si saputnik na putovanju i The naslednika na porodicu, O Allah, uzimam utočište sa vama teškoće putovanja, a sa imati promena od srca, i da budem u loše smetnja, i sam utočište u iz bolesna sudbinski izlaz dolazite sa bogatstvo i porodicu.

trans-unit.source: We have ended a new day and with it all dominion is Allah's. Praise is to Allah. None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, Who has no partner. To Allah belongs the dominion, and to Him is the praise and He is Able to do all things. My Lord, I ask You for the good things of this night and of the nights that come after it, and I seek refuge in You from the evil of this night and of the nights that come after it. My lord, I seek refuge in You from laziness and helpless old age. My Lord, I seek refuge in You from the punishment of Hell-fire, and from the punishment of the grave.
trans-unit.target: Kraju smo novi dan i sa njim sva vlast je Alahova. Pohvala je Alah. Niko nema pravo koju je trebalo obožavati osim Alaha sama, koji nema partnera. Da Allah Dominioni i pripada, da ga pohvalama i da je on je sposoban da radim sve stvari. Moj gospodaru, da vas zamolim za dobre stvari od ove noći, kao i od noći to dolaziti po njega, i trazim utociste u tebe od zla ove noći i noći koje dolaze po njega. Moj gospodaru, trazim utociste u tebe iz lenjosti i bespomoćni starost. Moj gospodaru, trazim utociste u tebi od kazne u paklu, a od kazne na grobu.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, You bring us the end of the day as You bring us its beginning, You bring us life and You bring us death, and to You is our fate.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, si nas doveo do kraja dana dok ste nas doveli početka, donesi nam život i ti nas smrt, i da li nam je sudbina.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, I have ended another day and call upon You and upon the bearers of Your Throne, upon Your angels and all creation to bear witness that surely You are Allah, there is none worthy of worship but You alone, You have no partners, and that Muhammad is Your slave and Your messenger. (Recite four times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: O Allah, sam prekinuo neki drugi dan, i pozivam vas i na nosioci vaša tron, na svoje anđele i sve kreacije da svedoci da sigurno ste Alaha, tamo nije dostojan molitve, ali vi sami, imate partnera, i da je Muhamed Ali tvoj rob i tvoj glasnik. (Recitovati 4 puta na arapskom).

trans-unit.source: O Allah, as I enter this evening whatever blessing has been received by me or anyone of Your creation is from You alone, You have no partner. All praise is for You and thanks is to You.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, kako da unesem ovo veče god blagoslov stigla je do mene, ili je neko tvoje tvorevine iz te sami, imate nema partnera. Sve pohvale je za tebe, i hvala ti je.

trans-unit.source: We have ended a new day and with it all the dominion which belongs to Allah, Lord of all that exists. O Allah, I ask You for the good things of this night, its victory, its help, its light, its blessings, and its guidance. I seek refuge in You from the evil that is in it and from the evil that follows it.
trans-unit.target: Kraju smo novi dan i sa njim sva vlast koja pripada Alahu, gospodaru svega što postoji. O Allah, da vas zamolim za dobre stvari u ovu, Pobjeda, njenu pomoć, njena svetlost, njegov blagoslov, i Severnjaиa. Trazim utociste u tebe od zla koje je u njoj, kao i od zla koje ih prati.

trans-unit.source: We end this day upon the natural religion of Islam, the word of sincere devotion, the religion of our Prophet Muhammad (peace and blessings of Allah be upon him), and the faith of our father Ibrahim. He was upright (in worshipping Allah), and a Muslim. He was not of those who worship others besides Allah.
trans-unit.target: Završavamo ovaj dan nad prirodnim lslam, reč iskrene odanosti, religiju nam proroka Muhameda (mir i blagoslov Alahov na njemu) i veru u naš otac Ibrahim. On je bio uspravni (u oboћavanje Allah) i musliman. On nije bio od onih koji se klanjaju drugi osim Allah.

trans-unit.source: I seek refuge in the Perfect Words of Allah from the evil of what He has created. (Recite three times in Arabic).
trans-unit.target: Trazim utociste u savršeno reči Allah od zla stvorio je. (Izgovori tri puta na arapskom).

trans-unit.source: We have risen this evening and sovereignty is all Allah’s. Praise is due to Allah alone, He has no partner, there is no God but Him, unto whom is our fate.
trans-unit.target: Smo vaskrsnuo večeras i suverenitet je sve Allah. Pohvala je Allah sama, ima nema partnera, nema Boga, ali ga, do koga nam je sudbina.

trans-unit.source: O Allah! I rise up in the evening with the blessing, strength, and protection, all of which you have bestowed upon me. Complete your blessing, the strength (you bestowed upon me) and your protection, in this life and the hereafter.
trans-unit.target: O Allah! Ustao sam u vece sa blagoslovom, snage i zaštite, koje si mi darovao. Dovršite svoj blagoslov, snage (si mi darovao) i vaše zaštite, u ovom životu i nadalje.

trans-unit.source: We have entered a new day and with it all dominion is Allah's. Praise is to Allah. None has the right to be worshipped but Allah alone, Who has no partner. My Lord, I ask You for the goodness of this day and of the days that come after it, and I seek refuge in You from the evil of this day and of the days that come after it. trans-unit.source: O Allah, by You we enter the morning and by You we enter the evening, by You we live and by You we die, and to You is the Final Return.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, od vas ćemo ući u jutro i od tebe smo unesite večeri, tako da živimo i da umremo, i da ti je "konačnog povratka".

I keep Your covenant, and my pledge to You so far as I am able, I seek refuge in You from the evil of what I have done, I admit to Your blessings upon me, and I admit to my misdeeds. trans-unit.source: Verily all praise is for Allah, we praise Him, seek His help and guidance and His forgiveness; and we seek refuge in Allah from the evil of ourselves and from the sinfulness of our actions. Whosoever Allah guides, then none can misguide him, and whosoever Allah misguides, there can be no guide for him. I testify there is no deity worthy of worship except Allah alone, and I testify that Muhammad is His servant and messenger.
trans-unit.target: Zaista sve pohvale za Alaha, hvalimo ga, tražiti njegovu pomoć i za vođenje i njegov oproštaj; i smo sklonili na Allah od zla nas samih i od greљnosti naše akcije. Ko god je Allah vodi, onda nijedan možete uznemirava ga, i ko god je Allah misguides, može da postoji bez Vodič za njega. Ja svedociti je dostojan molitvu osim Alaha sama bez boћanstvo, i da svedoči da je Muhamed je njegov sluga i glasnik.

trans-unit.source: To proceed: Certainly the best speech is the Book of Allah and the finest guidance is the guidance of Muhammad, the prayers of Allah upon him and peace. The most evil affair is a newly invented matter in religion and every newly invented matter is innovation and every innovation is straying and every straying is in the fire.
trans-unit.target: Da biste nastavili: sigurno najbolji govor knjigu Alaha i najbolji Vodič je vođstvom Muhameda, molitve Allah nad njim i mir. Zli afera je nedavno izmiљljen pitanje u religiji i svaki nedavno izmiљljen materija je inovacija i svaka inovacija odstupa i svakog odstupanja je u vatri.

Praise is to Allah Who gives us life after He has caused us to die and to Him is the return.
trans-unit.target: Pohvala je Alahu koji nam daje život, nakon što je izazvao nas da umremo i da mu je povratak.

trans-unit.source: There is none worthy of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner. His is the dominion and to Him belongs all praise, and He is Able to do all things. Glory is to Allah. Praise is to Allah. There is none worthy of worship but Allah. Allah is the Most Great. There is no might and no power except by Allah's leave, the Exalted, the Mighty. My Lord, forgive me.
trans-unit.target: To nije dostojan molitve ali Allah sama, koji nema partnera. Njegov je Dominioni mu pripada sva slava i on je sposoban da radim sve stvari. Slava je Alah. Pohvala je Alah. To nije dostojan molitve ali Allah. Alah je veoma veliki. Tamo je nema snage i nema struje, osim uz Alahovu dopuštenje, Exalted, silnog. Gospodaru moj, oprosti mi.

trans-unit.source: Praise is to Allah Who gave strength to my body and returned my soul to me and permitted me to remember Him.
trans-unit.target: Pohvala je Alahu koji je dao snagu da moje telo i da mi vrati moju dušu i dozvoljeno mi je da ga pamtim.

trans-unit.source: Praise is to Allah Who has clothed me with this (garment) (3x) and provided it for me, though I was powerless myself and incapable.
trans-unit.target: Pohvala je Alah ko je da mi odenuta sa (halje) (3 x) i da nam je to dao za mene, iako ja nisam mogao sebe i nesposobni.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, praise is to You. You have clothed me. I ask You for its goodness and the goodness of what it has been made for, and I seek Your protection from the evil of it and the evil of what it has been made for.
trans-unit.target: O Allah, hvaljen je na tebi. Uzimao si me. Ja te pitam za svoju dobrotu i dobrote je postignut, i sam tražiti tvoju zaštitu iz Uf, i od kako sam zla.

trans-unit.source: Glory to my Lord the Exalted (3x).
Glory is to You, O Allah, our Lord, and praise is Yours. O Allah, forgive me.
trans-unit.target: Slava je za tebe, O Allah, Gospod i pohvale je tvoj. O Allah, oprosti mi.

trans-unit.source: Glory (to You), Most Holy (are You), Lord of the angels and the Spirit.
trans-unit.target: Slava (ti), Najsvetija (si), gospodar anđeli i duh.

trans-unit.source: O Allah, to You I bow (in prayer) and in You I believe and to You I have submitted. Before You my hearing is humbled, as is my sight, my mind, my bones, my nerves and what my feet have mounted upon (for travel).
trans-unit.target: O Allah, tebi klanjam (u molitvi) i u tebi verujem i tebi predalo. Pred vama moj sluh je ponizna, kao i vida, moj um, moje kosti, živce, a šta moja stopala skamenio na (na putovanju).

trans-unit.source: Glory is to You, Master of power, of dominion, of majesty and greatness.
trans-unit.target: Slava je za tebe, gospodar moć, vlast, Veličanstvo i velicinu.
